Moreover, Luigioni (1929) recorded this species generically for central and southern Italy; generic records for northern and peninsular Italy ( Audisio et al. 1995 ) and for "Italy" ( Kadej 2005 ,
Hava 2007
) refer to the above regions, the same is probably valid for a generic record for mainland Italy ( Zhantiev 2011a ).
